<li id="cite_note-65"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-65">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith_Jr.manuscript_by_Willard_Richards,_George_A._Smith_and_their_assistants_as_finished_in_1858" class="citation book cs1">Smith Jr., Joseph; manuscript by Willard Richards, George A. Smith and their assistants as finished in 1858. <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Henry_Roberts" class="mw-redirect" title="Brigham Henry Roberts">Roberts, Brigham Henry</a> (ed.). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://byustudies.byu.edu/hc/hcpgs/hc.aspx"><i>History of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</i></a>. Vol.&#160;2. Salt Lake City, Utah: Deseret Book Company<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">15 June</span> 2009</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book+Company&amp;rft.aulast=Smith+Jr.&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rft.au=manuscript+by+Willard+Richards%2C+George+A.+Smith+and+their+assistants+as+finished+in+1858&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbyustudies.byu.edu%2Fhc%2Fhcpgs%2Fhc.aspx&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATeachings+of+Joseph+Smith" class="Z3988"></span><span class="cs1-maint citation-comment"><code class="cs1-code">{{<a href="/wiki/Template:Cite_book" title="Template:Cite book">cite book</a>}}</code>:  CS1 maint: numeric names: authors list (<a href="/wiki/Category:CS1_maint:_numeric_names:_authors_list" title="Category:CS1 maint: numeric names: authors list">link</a>)</span> Provided by BYU Studies. Published in book form under the direction of the First Presidency in 1902<br />&#160;&#160;
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTandy" class="citation journal cs1">Tandy, Jon. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.centerplace.org/library/study/dc/ldc-marr.htm">"Differences between the RLDS and LDS Doctrine and Covenants on the subject of Marriage"</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">December 26,</span> 2008</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Differences+between+the+RLDS+and+LDS+Doctrine+and+Covenants+on+the+subject+of+Marriage&amp;rft.aulast=Tandy&amp;rft.aufirst=Jon&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.centerplace.org%2Flibrary%2Fstudy%2Fdc%2Fldc-marr.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATeachings+of+Joseph+Smith" class="Z3988"></span> <span class="cs1-visible-error citation-comment"><code class="cs1-code">{{<a href="/wiki/Template:Cite_journal" title="Template:Cite journal">cite journal</a>}}</code>: </span><span class="cs1-visible-error citation-comment">Cite journal requires <code class="cs1-code">&#124;journal=</code> (<a href="/wiki/Help:CS1_errors#missing_periodical" title="Help:CS1 errors">help</a>)</span><br />&#160;&#160;These citations refer to <a href="/wiki/Doctrine_and_Covenants#Portions_removed_from_the_LDS_edition" title="Doctrine and Covenants">Section 101:4</a> of the 1835 Kirtland Edition, section CIX in the 1844 Nauvoo Edition and Section 111 in the 1950 Reorganized Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints version. They reads: "Inasmuch as this church of Christ has been reproached with the crime of fornication, and polygamy: we declare that we believe, that one man should have one wife; and one woman, but one husband." This section was removed from the LDS Church's publication of the Doctrine and Covenants in 1876 along with the insertion of Section 132 describing the new and everlasting covenant, including the plurality of wives. (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/132?lang=eng">D&amp;C 132 Intro</a>)</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-66"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-66">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPeregoMyers,_Natalie_M.;_and_Woodward,_Scott_R.2005" class="citation journal cs1">Perego, Ugo A.; Myers, Natalie M.; and Woodward, Scott R. (2005-05-29). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20060725191602/http://mha.wservers.com/pubs/TOC/05_July_Journal_TOC.pdf">"Reconstructing the Y-Chromosome of Joseph Smith Jr.: Genealogical Applications; Remembering the Wives of Joseph Smith"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Mormon_History" class="mw-redirect" title="Journal of Mormon History">Journal of Mormon History</a></i>. <b>32</b> (2): 70–88. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://mha.wservers.com/pubs/TOC/05_July_Journal_TOC.pdf">the original</a> <span class="cs1-format">(<a href="/wiki/PDF" title="PDF">PDF</a> of Table of Contents only)</span> on 2006-07-25<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2006-07-02</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Mormon+History&amp;rft.atitle=Reconstructing+the+Y-Chromosome+of+Joseph+Smith+Jr.%3A+Genealogical+Applications%3B+Remembering+the+Wives+of+Joseph+Smith&amp;rft.volume=32&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=70-88&amp;rft.date=2005-05-29&amp;rft.aulast=Perego&amp;rft.aufirst=Ugo+A.&amp;rft.au=Myers%2C+Natalie+M.%3B+and+Woodward%2C+Scott+R.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmha.wservers.com%2Fpubs%2FTOC%2F05_July_Journal_TOC.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATeachings+of+Joseph+Smith" class="Z3988"></span><span class="cs1-maint citation-comment"><code class="cs1-code">{{<a href="/wiki/Template:Cite_journal" title="Template:Cite journal">cite journal</a>}}</code>:  CS1 